{
  "stem": "7094.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I didn't know how to, but the only way-- I knew they lived in Sanok, which is another town.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when I came back to Poland, I wrote a letter to the-- to the-- to the town hall that I'm looking for these people, because I knew that they will come back.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I made contact with them and I'm in touch with them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the Russian-- you know, the war between Germany and Russia broke out in June '41, 22nd of June.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were on the border, so the first day the German came out straightaway.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, this was a different German army who came and a different attitude.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The first year, we prepared a lot of food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We knew that war, any war-- we didn't know about the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But as soon as came in, the Germans came in, we tried to-- to save-- to-- to have stock of food.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The first winter was bearable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, most men were taken to labor and also the women.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I used to have to go to work every day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We used to come to Judenrat and we used to be sent to different work, cleaning the streets, snow in the winter, cleaning up from the snow, carrying some ammunition at the railway station, working all kind.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Cleaning offices, that was the main thing for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you could see my school friends sitting, because they were mostly Ukrainian who were now in charge.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Ukrainian collaborated, because the German promised them a independent Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They didn't keep their promise.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But because of that, they collaborated with Germany very much and they could vent their native-- the inherent anti-Semitism was opportunity for expressing it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they had the power.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
